  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Extreme Weather and Disaster Preparedness to Enhance the Resilience of Host and Rohingya Communities in Cox&apos;S Bazar, Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this action is to strengthen Disaster Risk Management (DRM) and response capacity at the Upazila, District, and Union level in host communities and enhance the disaster resilience of host and Rohingya communities in Teknaf and Ukhia, (Cox&#x2019;s bazar, Bangladesh). This Action will consist of activities falling under five results: 1) Strengthened DRM capacity of Host Communities; 2) Strengthened DRM capacity of community and camp volunteers; 3) Risk-informed upgrading of shelters and reinforcement of community-level structures; 4) Small scale site development and mitigation works and large scale (cut and fill) earthworks in unoccupied zones to increase useable area and reduce the risk of landslide; and 5) Technical capacity is in place to advise humanitarian actors on disaster risk management within the local context.</narrative>
  </description>
